#cli #spec #built

> diagnose command — graph health checks for orphans, bloat, hubs, broken edges and stubs.

Run with: `eshp diagnose`

## Checks

orphaned nodes
  Notes with zero edges (no incoming, no outgoing). Islands in the graph.
  Likely need to be linked to related notes, or may be stale/redundant.

bloated notes  (body > 2000 chars)
  Good candidates for splitting into multiple focused notes or summarising.
  Long notes reduce recall precision and overwhelm the LLM context window.

hub nodes  (degree > 2× mean AND degree ≥ 5)
  Notes with far more connections than average. May need to be decomposed
  or the edges may be over-specified. Often legitimate architecture hubs.

dangling edges
  Edges where src or dst does not exist in the notes table. Should normally
  be empty (orphan cleanup in upsert_note handles these), but worth checking.

bare notes  (no desc line)
  Notes with no > summary line. The desc is used in scan results, rels output,
  and LLM summaries — a missing desc degrades discoverability.

tagless notes  (no tags)
  Notes with no #tags. Tags drive `eshp tag` filtering and top-tag stats.

stub notes  (no body AND no desc)
  Completely empty notes — likely created but never filled in.

redundant rel pairs  (≥2 mirrored edge pairs)
  Pairs of relationship types that are always exact inverses of each other,
  e.g. every "manages" edge has a matching "managed-by" edge and vice versa.
  These redundant two-way relationships add noise without adding information.
  Pick one direction and delete all edges of the other type.
  Requires ≥2 pairs to avoid false positives on coincidental single mirrors.

## Output format

Structured CLI output: one section per check category. Healthy checks are
suppressed (only shown with --verbose). Issues are prefixed with ⚠ or 💡.
A summary line at the end shows issue count and healthy check count.

## Thresholds (defaults)

  bloated_chars: 2000
  hub_factor:    2.0   (degree must exceed mean × hub_factor)
  hub_min_deg:   5     (hubs must have at least this many edges to qualify)
  stub_chars:    50    (body shorter than this counts as no-body)

## Usage in skills

commit-and-dream: run diagnose, address critical issues (dangling edges,
  orphaned nodes) if time permits; note others for next deep-dream.
deep-dream: run diagnose first, treat output as the work queue.
  Work through all issues, preferring orphan linking and bloat splitting.

